This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object tracking, which is a common task in computer vision. It also involves data association, which is a key challenge in multi-target tracking. The paper also mentions autonomous driving, which is a popular application of computer vision. 

The paper could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it deals with tracking objects in real-time, which is important for robots to navigate their environment. 

The use of Dirichlet Processes and Bayesian models suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper's focus on real-time tracking and the use of a temporal dependence suggests that it could also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
